  "prompt": "How much time does Deloitte generally takes to get back after interview?",
  "response": "The time Deloitte takes to get back to candidates after an interview can vary depending on several factors, such as the specific role, the number of candidates being interviewed, the level of the position, and the overall hiring process. Generally speaking, candidates might hear back anywhere from a few days to a couple of weeks after their interview. \n\nIt's not uncommon for large firms like Deloitte to have multiple rounds of interviews, and there might be some delays due to coordination and decision-making processes.\n\nIf you haven't heard back within two weeks, it might be a good idea to follow up with your recruiter or the HR contact person to inquire about the status of your application. This shows your continued interest in the position and can provide you with more information on the timeline.",
